    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Open spaces in rooms that allow for unencumbered movement within them. Circulation spaces can occupy a percentage of a room, or be constructed for the singular purpose of allowing free circulation. For outdoor pedestrian circulation pathways see terms collocated under "walkways".</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
